{{For|Blue's News|Chelsea TV}} {{ref improve|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox Magazine | title = Blues News | image_file = | image_size = | image_caption = | editor = Petri Hoppula | editor_title = Chief editor | frequency = Bi-monthly | circulation = | category = Music magazine | company = | publisher = | firstdate = 12 July 1968 | country = Finland | based = [[Helsinki]] | language = Finnish | website = [http://www.bluesnews.fi www.bluesnews.fi] | issn = 0784-7726 }}
'''''Blues News''''' is a bi-monthly [[Finland|Finnish]] [[blues]] and roots music [[magazine]].
==History and profile== ''Blues News'' was founded in 1968, making it one of the oldest blues magazines still in print in the world. The magazine is published by Finnish Blues Society (FBS ry). The FBS is a [[Non-profit journalism|non-profitable association]], sponsored by the Ministry of Culture and the City of Helsinki. The name of the society was changed to Suomen afroamerikkalaisen musiikin yhdistys (SAMY ry) in 1980. In 2006, the name reverted to the original ''FBS''. The Society has a its own record label, Blue North Records.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Blues News - Finnish Blues Magazine|url = http://www.bluesnews.fi/introduction.htm|website=www.bluesnews.fi|accessdate=22 November 2015}}</ref>
