The '''Embassy of Slovenia''' in [[London]] is the [[diplomatic mission]] of [[Slovenia]] in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/263519/LDL_December_2013.pdf |title=The London Diplomatic List |date=14 December 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211155353/https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/263519/LDL_December_2013.pdf |archivedate=2013-12-11 |df= }}</ref> It was opened in 1992, one year after Slovenia declared independence from [[Yugoslavia]].<ref>{{cite news | url= http://www.london.embassy.si/index.php?id=210&L=1  | title= About the Embassy | date=28 November 2013}}</ref> Previously on [[Little College Street]], it later moved to [[Dartmouth Street]].

