{{Infobox mountain | name = Gross Fusshorn | photo = Geisshorn.1745a.jpg | photo_caption = The Gross Fusshorn (left) and the [[Geisshorn]] (centre-left) from the south side | elevation_m = 3627 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 123 | prominence_ref = <ref>Retrieved from the [[Swisstopo]] topographic maps. The key col is located north of the summit at 3,504 metres.</ref> | parent_peak = [[Aletschhorn]] | map = Switzerland | map_caption = Location in Switzerland | location = [[Valais]], [[Switzerland]] | range = [[Bernese Alps]] | coordinates = {{coord|46|25|49.3|N|7|59|52.8|E|type:mountain_region:CH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
The '''Gross Fusshorn''' is a [[mountain]] of the [[Bernese Alps]], overlooking the [[Oberaletsch Glacier]] in the canton of [[Valais]]. The Fusshörner are a group of peaks located on the south ridge of the Gross Fusshorn. On the east side lies a glacier named ''Driestgletscher''.
