{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox single | Name = Há dias Assim | Cover = Filipa-ha_dias_assim.jpg | Border = yes | Artist = [[Filipa Azevedo]] | Released = 2010 | Format = [[Digital single]], [[CD single]] | Recorded = 2010 | Genre = | Length = 2:57 | Label = | Writer = [[Augusto Madureira]] | Producer = | Chart position = | Last single = | This single = | Next single = | Misc = {{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{Flag icon|Portugal}} "Há dias assim" | image = | caption = | year = 2010 | country = Portugal | artist = [[Filipa Azevedo]] | as = | with = | language = Portuguese | composer = [[Augusto Madureira]] | lyricist = [[Augusto Madureira]] | place = 18th | points = 43 | place_semi = 4th | points_semi = 89 | lyrics = | prev = Todas as Ruas do Amor | prev_link = Todas as Ruas do Amor | next = A luta é alegria | next_link = A luta é alegria }} }} "'''Há dias assim'''" ({{IPA-pt|a ˈdiɐz ɐˈsĩ}}, translation:''There are days like this'', English title: ''It's One of Those Days'') is a song composed by [[Augusto Madureira]] and performed by [[Filipa Azevedo]], and represented [[Portugal]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2010]] in May 2010 in [[Oslo]], [[Norway]]. It's a song that talks about the loneliness of the people by the outside world. The song was the winner of the 2010 [[Festival da Canção]] contest, receiving maximum votes from the juries. The song competed for Portugal in the first semi-final of Eurovision 2010, where Filipa Azevedo performed 14th in the running order, following Greece's [[Giorgos Alkaios|Giorgos Alkaios and Friends]] with "[[OPA (song)|OPA]]" and preceding Macedonia's [[Gjoko Taneski]] with "[[Jas ja imam silata]]". "Há dias assim" qualified for the final round, where she performed 23rd in the running order after Germany's [[Lena Meyer-Landrut]] with "[[Satellite (Lena Meyer-Landrut song)|Satellite]]" (who would eventually win) and preceding Israel's [[Harel Skaat]] with "[[Milim]]". The song finished 18th with 43 points.<ref name="Portugal 1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=10053&_t=Portugal+decided%3A+Filipa+Azevedo+to+Oslo!!!|title=Portugal decided: Filipa Azevedo to Oslo!!!|last=Escudero |first=Victor M.|date=7 March 2010|publisher=''[[European Broadcasting Union]]''|accessdate=7 March 2010}}</ref>
