{{Infobox museum | name = Lithuanian Road Museum | native_name = Kelių Muziejus | native_name_lang = lt | image = | imagesize = 200 | caption = | alt = | coordinates = {{coord|54|46|20.77|N|24|48|50.05|E|type:landmark_region:LT|display=inline,title}} | established = {{Start date|1995|10|19|df=y}} | location = Kauno g. 14, LT-21372, [[Vievis]], Elektrėnų savivaldybė, [[Lithuania]] | type = Industrial | collection = | visitors = | director = Juozas Stepankevičius | curator = | owner = | website = {{URL|www.automagistrale.lt/index.php/lt/keliu-muzejus}} }}
The '''Lithuanian Road Museum''' ({{lang-lt|Kelių Muziejus}}) is a museum in [[Lithuania]] that collects, displays and interprets objects related to [[road building]].<ref name="Jeary">{{cite web|url=http://worldnews.nbcnews.com/_news/2013/05/05/18020379-roadkill-rocks-and-russian-tanks-inside-one-of-the-worlds-oddest-museums|title=Roadkill, rocks and Russian tanks: Inside one of the world's oddest museums - World News|last=Jeary|first=Peter|date=2013-05-05|work=[[NBCNews.com]]|accessdate=6 May 2013}}</ref><ref name="MoL">{{cite web|url=http://www.muziejai.lt/Elektrenai/keliu_muziejus.en.htm|title=The Roads Museum|accessdate=6 May 2013}}</ref> It is located in the premises of the state highway organisation, "{{lang|lt|Automagistralė}}", in [[Vievis]], near the main road between [[Vilnius]] and [[Kaunas]] and opened on the 25th anniversary of the road's completion,<ref name="Jeary" /> on 19 October 1995.<ref name="MoL" />
The collection of approximately 6,000 objects<ref name="Jeary" /> includes models, tools, plant, protective clothing, road signs and documents.<ref name="MoL" />
The museum's founder, director and curator is Juozas Stepankevičius, a former road engineer and construction manager.<ref name="Jeary" /><ref name="MoL" />
