{{Infobox Union |name= Norwegian Airline Pilots Association |country= [[Norway]] |affiliation= [[International Federation of Air Line Pilots' Associations|IFALPA]] |members= 850 |full_name= Norwegian Airline Pilots Association |native_name= Norsk Flygerforbund |image= [[File:Norwegian Airline Pilots Association.jpg]] |founded= 1977 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= Drammensveien 43, N-0271 OSLO |people= [[Helge O. Anonsen]], leader |website= [http://www.flyger.no http://www.flyger.no] |footnotes= }}
The '''Norwegian Airline Pilots Association''' ({{lang-no|Norsk Flygerforbund}}, NF) is a [[trade union]] of civil airline pilots in [[Norway]].
It was established as a merger in 1977. It has about 850 members,<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Norsk Journalistlag|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|editor=Henriksen, Petter|url=http://www.snl.no/Norsk_Journalistlag|language=Norwegian|accessdate=3 October 2009}}</ref> and has its headquarters in Drammensveien at Skillebekk, Oslo.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://flyger.no/omoss/|title=Velkommen|last=Anonsen|first=Helge O.|publisher=Norwegian Airline Pilots Association|language=Norwegian|accessdate=3 October 2009}}</ref> It is a member body of the [[International Federation of Air Line Pilots' Associations]], IFALPA.<ref name=snl/>
Civil airlines pilots in Norway have also been members of the [[Confederation of Vocational Unions]] due to dissatisfaction with the Norwegian Airline Pilots Association.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.boarding.no/art.asp?id=20039|title=Ex-Braathens-piloter ut av Norsk Flygerforbund|date=26 January 2006|work=[[Boarding.no]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=3 October 2009}}</ref>
