{{Infobox Union |name= Fastighets |country= [[Sweden]] |affiliation= [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation|LO]] |members= 40,000 |full_name= Swedish Building Maintenance Workers' Union |native_name= Fastighetsanställdas Förbund |image= [[Image:Fastighets logo.png|100px]] |founded= 1936 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Stockholm]], Sweden |people= [[Hans Öhlund]], president |website= [http://www.fastighets.se www.fastighets.se] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Swedish Building Maintenance Workers' Union''' (Fastighets) is a [[trade union]] in [[Sweden]]. It was formed in 1936 and has a membership of 40,000.
Fastighets represents building maintenance workers employed by private, cleaners in cleaning companies, window cleaners and employees of Folkets Hus ([[Labour Movement Community Centres]]).
Fastighets is affiliated with the [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation]], and [[Union Network International]].
==References== *{{cite book | year = 2005 | title = Trade Unions of the World | editor = [[International Centre for Trade Union Rights|ICTUR]] et al., | edition = 6th | publisher = John Harper Publishing | location = London, UK | isbn = 0-9543811-5-7 }}
==External links== * [http://www.fastighets.se Fastighets] official site.
