'''Thomas Moodie''' (29 November 1839 - 30 April 1894) was a pioneer who in 1892 led a party of mostly Afrikaner farmers from the [[Orange Free State]] to settle in [[Rhodesia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.geni.com/projects/Moodie-Trek-to-Rhodesia-1892/14431|title=Moodie Trek to Rhodesia - 1892|accessdate=1 June 2017|publisher=Geni}}</ref> Moodie, known as "Groot Tom", left [[Bethlehem, Free State|Bethlehem]] on 5 May 1892 with his party, and settled on 4 January 1893, establishing the town of [[Melsetter]], named after the Moodie ancestral home in the [[Orkney Islands]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Geldenhuys Genealogy, Descendants of Albert Barends Gildenhuizen|first=Preller|last=Geldenhuys|date=2015}}</ref>

